ve-amazon-jungle-17-days-after-plane-crash?utm_source=rss_feed<author><![CDATA[Agence France-Presse]]></author><category>消息</category><category>世界</category><category>飞机失事和航空事故</category><category>航空</category><category>美洲</category><category>四个孩子</category><category>包括婴儿</category><category>飞机失事 17 天后在亚马逊丛林中被发现还活着</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[No flying high for Japan’s post-Covid airports, with tourists greeted by lack of staff and queues]]></title><description><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/japan?utm_source=google_amp&amp;utm_medium=Off-Platform-referrals&amp;utm_campaign=3220954_inline_link" title="" data-entity-uuid="73990659-b9b2-48a9-b582-fdf28ced9714" data-entity-type="taxonomy_term" data-entity-bundle="topics">日本</a>机场的重新开放受到了国内旅游业的欢迎，近几个月来外国<a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/tourism?utm_source=google_amp&amp;utm_medium=Off-Platform-referrals&amp;utm_campaign=3220954_inline_link" title="" data-entity-uuid="e61d5d51-e69c-463a-aca0-e5475821442e" data-entity-type="taxonomy_term" data-entity-bundle="topics">游客</a>人数<a href="https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/economics/article/3216975/japan-rammed-tourists-and-chinese-visitors-arent-even-back-full-force?utm_source=google_amp&amp;utm_medium=Off-Platform-referrals&amp;utm_campaign=3220954_inline_link" title="" data-entity-uuid="9c2631ba-6214-4204-afbf-4f3725af3903" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-bundle="article">激增</a>，尽管由于地面严重短缺，行李转运延误和安检排长队使游客回国蒙上阴影职员。</p><p>当美国的机场在全球冠状病毒大流行的早期阶段实际上陷入停顿时，数百名机场工作人员离开了该部门。 </p><div class="meter__linear relative" id="default-meter-page-views-11"><img width="auto" height="1" src="https://www.scmp.com/images/1x1.png" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><div class="dm__l3"><hr class="vertical-line"><div class="dm__lw"><svg class="dm__l" height="24" viewBox="0 0 18 24" width="18" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><g style="stroke:#000;fill:none;fill-rule:evenodd;stroke-linecap:round;stroke-linejoin:round;stroke-width:1.5"><rect height="13.5" rx="1.5"